Syntax for Lambda Expression

1.If a Function contains no arguments
let funName = () => { // Body of the function}

2.If a Function has only one Arguments
let funName = (a) => {Body of the function};
OR
Round Brackets for the argument can be optional for this case.

let funName = a => {Body of the function};

3. If a function has more than one argument

let funName =(a,b,c) => {Body of the function}

4. If a function has only a return expression then the body of the function is
   Optional
   let funName = () => return expression alone
